    "In cases where graph structure or node importance is difficult to estimate, this could lead to suboptimal retrieval performance.",
    "As shown in Figure 4, a 2-gop ego-graph is transformed into a nested, indented list, which mirrors the graph's structure.",
    "Each level in the hierarchy corresponds to a level in the graph, representing connections between nodes.",
    "For example, \"NODE 1\" contains sub-nodes (NODE 1.1, NODE 1.2, etc.",
    "), which are further divided into lower levels, reflecting the original graph's branching structure."
